The world biodiversity of palpigrades remains largely unknown despite the enormous progress seen in the last 15–20 years. There are 114 species described to date (Bu et al. 2019; Souza & Ferreira 2020 ; Souza et al. 2020;
Bu et al. 2021
, in press), a number remarkably smaller as compared to other groups of arachnids; for example, there are about 2200 known species of scorpions ( Lourenço 2018 ), 220 of whip spiders (Amplypygi) (
Shakhatreh et al. 2020
), and 1200 of sun spiders (Solifugae) (
Botero-Trujillo et al . 2017
).

